                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2309: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="to"
                            >Caffery</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-22T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 22, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Your 74, September 21, 4 p.m. In informal discussion of certain of the
                    Neutrals it was suggested that they would ask their Governments to advise their
                    representatives at Geneva fully regarding the Chaco negotiations in order that
                    they would have the full background should the matter be brought up at the
                    League meeting. Department has no suggestion to make regarding endeavor to
                    persuade other Latin American delegates to instruct their delegates also but
                    leaves this matter to <persName corresp="#p_OHE1">Olaya</persName>. The question
                    has not been raised here. The only point discussed was that the representatives
                    at the League of the Neutral Governments, members of the League, should be fully
                    informed of the situation so that they could handle it if it is brought up.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
